metadata.name: Entomopia-1
metadata.description:
The name Entomopia is a combination of two words "Entomo" which is derived from Greek language meaning insect and "opia" meaning a place of visual or mental imagery, or a place of vivid, imaginative representation. 
Entomopia perfectly captures the essence of the planet being rich in insect life, it also implies a place of vivid and imaginative representation of these creatures.
